</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium italicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="italicum">Arthrinium italicum</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. thailandicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="thailandicum">A. thailandicum</taxonomicName>
, and to a lesser extent to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. malaysianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="malaysianum">A. malaysianum</taxonomicName>
. Stromata of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. thailandicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="thailandicum">A. thailandicum</taxonomicName>
are smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. italicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="italicum">A. italicum</taxonomicName>
, measuring 0.45-0.99 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.55 mm, ascomata are perithecical, its conidiogenous cells are longer (11.5-39 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and branched, and conidia measure 5-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. The conidia of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. malaysianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="malaysianum">A. malaysianum</taxonomicName>
are similar in size, but this species does not produce conidiophores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
